definition.value: A benzoate ester obtained by condensation of benzoic acid and methanol.
A germacrane sesquiterpenoid derived from germacrane by dehydrogenation between the 1-10 and 4-5 positions as well as hydroxylation at position 6.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 7,8-dihydroneopterin 2'-phosphate.
An organophosphate oxoanion obtained by deprotonation of the phosphate OH groups of 4-(beta-D-ribofuranosyl)aminobenzene 5'-phosphate.
A leukotriene that is the 11-trans-isomer of leukotriene E4.
A precorrin carboxylic acid anion obtained by global deprotonation of the carboxy groups of cobalt-precorrin-6B.
A 6-O-acyl-D-glucose that is the 6-O-(4-hydroxy-2-methylenebutanoyl) derivative of D-glucopyranose.
The methyl ester of indole-3-acetic acid.
A trienoic fatty acid that consists of heptadeca-5,8,10-trienoic acid bearing an additional 12-hydroxy substituent.
A pterin phosphate that is 7,8-dihydroneopterin carrying a single monophosphate substituent at position 2'.
An HETE having a 9-hydroxy group and (5E)-, (7Z)-, (11Z)- and (14Z)-double bonds.
An HETE that is (5Z,7E,11Z,14Z)-icosa-5,7,11,14-tetraenoic acid in which the hydroxy group is located at position 9.
A ribose monophosphate that is 4-(beta-D-ribofuranosyl)aminobenzene carrying a single monophospate substituent at position 5'.
A carboxylic acid trianion resulting from the deprotonation of the phosphate group and both carboxy groups of 7,8-dihydromethanopterin. The major species at pH 7.3.
A C20 hydroxy polyunsaturated fatty acid having (5S)-, (6R)- and (15R)-hydroxy groups as well as (7E)- (9E)-, (11Z)- and (13E)-double bonds.
A long-chain polyunsaturated fatty acid that is any docosahexaenoic acid bearing a single hydroxy substituent. An oxidation product of docosahexaenoic acid metabolism.
An organosulfate oxoanion that is the conjugate base of lamellarin alpha 20-hydrogen sulfate.
A heterocyclyl sulfate that acts as a HIV-1 integrase inhibitor.
A long-chain polyunsaturated fatty acid that is any icosatrienoic acid bearing a single hydroxy substituent. An oxidation product of icosatrienoic acid metabolism.
A hydroxydocosahexaenoic acid that consists of 4Z,7Z,9E,13Z,16Z,19Z-docosahexaenoic acid with the hydroxy group located at position 11.
A leukotriene that is the 12S-isomer of leukotriene B4.
A kanamycin that is kanamycin A in which the 6'-amino group is replaced by a hydroxy group.
A long-chain polyunsaturated fatty acid that is any icosapentaenoic acid bearing a single hydroxy substituent. An oxidation product of icosapentaenoic acid metabolism.
A sphingoid that is sphingosine having an additional trans-double bond at position 8.
A hydroxyicosapentaenoic acid that consists of 6E,8Z,11Z,14Z,17Z-icosapentaenoic acid with the hydroxy group located at position 5.
A hydroxyicosapentaenoic acid that consists of 5Z,8Z,11Z,14Z,16E-icosapentaenoic acid with the hydroxy group located at position 18.
A 1-(alk-1-enyl)-2-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alk-1-enyl and acyl group are specified as (Z)-hexadec-1-enyl and hexadecanoyl (palmitoyl) respectively.
A long-chain polyunsaturated fatty acid that is any octadecatrienoic acid bearing a single hydroxy substituent. An oxidation product of octadecatrienoic acid metabolism.
A monoalkylglycerophosphocholine that is sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which the alkyl group is located at position 2.
An alkyl,acyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine having an acyl group at the 1 position and a (Z)-alk-1-enyl substituent at the 2-position.
A glycerophosphocholine that is sn-glycero-3-phosphocholine in which positions 1 and 2 are substituted by unspecified alkyl groups.
A hydroxyoctadecatrienoic acid that consists of 6Z,9Z,11E-octadecatrienoic acid having the hydroxy group located at position 13.
A purine 2'-deoxyribonucleoside in which a 2-deoxy-beta-D-ribofuranosyl residue is attached at position 9 of 9H-purine via a glycosidic linkage.
A fluorogenic cyanine dye in which N-(3-sulfopropyl)quinolinium is linked to a 1,3,3-trimethyldihydroindole via a propan-1-yl-3-ylidene chain to form a conjugated system.
An oxo fatty acid that is obtained by oxidation of the allylic hydroxy group of any hydroxyoctadecadienoic acid during its metabolism.
A biomacromolecule composed of carbohydrate residues which is secreted by a microorganism into the surrounding environment.
An indolyl carboxylic acid that is acetic acid in which one of the methyl hydrogens is substituted by an indol-1-yl group.
An oxooctadecadienoic acid that consists of 9E,11E-octadecadienoic acid with the oxo substituent located at position 13.
A dipeptide consisting of two L-alanine units joined by a peptide linkage.
A methyladenosine that is the 1-methyl-2-hydro derivative of adenosine.
An organofluorine compound that is the 5-fluoro derivative of indole.
A fatty acid ester obtained by formal condensation of the carboxy group of sorbic acid and the hydroxy group of ethanol.
A bromo fatty acid that is decanoic acid carrying a single bromo substituent at position 2.
A  tryptophan derivative that is tryptophan carrying a single methyl substituent at position 1 on the indole.
An aromatic ether that is quinoline substituted at position 6 by a methoxy group.
A zwitterion obtained by transfer of a proton from the phosphate to the amino group of any glycerophosphoethanolamine.
A 1-alkyl-sn-glycero-3-phosphoethanolamine in which the alkyl substituent can be any Z-alk-1-enyl group.
A 1-acyl-sn-glycero-3-phospho-(1'-sn-glycerol)(1-) in which the acyl group is specified as tetradecanoyl (myristoyl); major species at pH 7.3.
